						               													<description>From the back of the box : &amp;#10;25 cards Tarot wich harmonize between them to create an infinity of pictures.&amp;#10;VIA VITAE is also an original cardgame for 2 players.&amp;#10;Each card is an work of art specially performed by Dominique Ehrhard, Art painter and game designer.&amp;#10;In the box, a 24 pages booklet present various artist's works.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the rulebook : &amp;#10;VIA VITAE is published by Edition Face &amp;amp; Dos and the town of Issy-les-Moulineaux with the support of Incredible Toys.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It was a game specially created for an exposure about Dominique Ehrhard and his works of art called &amp;quot;The exposure where you play, paintings and games of Dominique Ehrhard&amp;quot;, from 8th december 2004 to 13th february 2005 at the French Museum of the Playing Card (city of Issy-les-Moulineaux).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game runs 2 rounds. Biggest score at the end of the second round wins.&amp;#10;Each round plays in the same way. A player lay a card face up, the other player must answers to this card by playing a card with the same color or the same symbol. The player who can't answers to the card played by his opponent lose the round.&amp;#10;Each card show a number from 1 to 5 under its colored symbol.&amp;#10;This number is the strength of the card. The player who plays the strongest card, continues and plays first with another card which calls another answer card...etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Paintings on cards have no influence on the game but show life line (via vitae) of players...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
